urldecode [URL]

Break a URL into its components (scheme, netloc, userinfo, host,
port, path, fragment) and percent-decode its query string, printing
one `key = value` line per query parameter.

The URL can be passed as an argument or on stdin (handy for piping
from the clipboard). Leading and trailing whitespace are trimmed.

Examples:

  urldecode 'https://example.com/p?a=1&b=hello%20world&b=again'
  pbpaste | urldecode

Requires: python3.
